<item>
  <title>Undefeated… Until It Mattered Most</title>
  <dc:creator>Kendal Hasemann</dc:creator>
  <link>https://your-website-url.example.com/posts/ncaa-volleyball-nebraska-2025-season/</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<p>Did Nebraska Volleyball Peak Too Early in the 2025 Season? Let’s see what the data has to say.</p>
<p>Upon first glance, people and fans may think that Nebraska Volleyball peaked early in the 2025 season. The offense shows flashes of dominance right out of the gate, with strong hitting percentages being apparent as early as September. But if you take a step back and look at the full season, the story becomes a little more complex.</p>
<p>The Huskers had quite the year, going undefeated in the regular season during their first year with Coach Dani Busboom Kelly. They opened the season with solid hitting performances, including multiple matches where the Huskers hit above .350 and some even pushing into the .400 range. That kind of success early on can give the impression that the team was already at its best.</p>
<p>However, those strong early games aren’t unique for Nebraska. As the season progressed into October and November, Nebraska continued to have equally strong, if not stronger offensive performances, including some of the highest hitting percentages of the whole season. The early games weren’t a peak, it was the beginning of a pattern of high level play.</p>
