<p>While the early season showed off some strong performances, it also showed variability, with some matches dipping closer to .250 or .300. As the season went on, those dips became less frequent, and high efficiency matches appeared more consistently.</p>
<p>This shows that Nebraska didn’t fade after a hot start to the season. Instead, they became more reliable offensively as the season progressed. If the Huskers had peaked early, we would expect to see defensive performance drop off later in the season.</p>
<p>But the relationship between digs and blocks remained relatively steady throughout. There’s no clear decline, just a consistent mix of performances, which tells us that the defense didn’t regress, it stayed stable, but not dominant all year.</p>
