<p>So, did Nebraska Peak Early?</p>
<p>The short answer is no.</p>
<p>The Huskers didn’t peak early. They sustained and even continued to build on their performances over the course of the 2025 season. They had a strong start and continued to play high level volleyball. They ended their season with an impressive 33-1. It was a year of growth and trying new things. It’s a season the girls should be proud of.</p>
<p>Nebraska’s strength and consistency carried them to an undefeated regular season, proving their offense and overall performance stayed steady from beginning to end. But the data also showed a vulnerability of theirs, inconsistency in errors and a defense that was steady, yet wasn’t always dominant.</p>
<p>In the end, that caught up to them. When Nebraska faced off against Texas A&amp;M in the Regional Final of the 2025 NCAA Women’s Volleyball Tournament, they fell short, losing 2 sets to 3 in a heartbreaker that ended their season.</p>
<p>The Huskers weren’t a team that faded out after a strong start to their season. They were a team whose strengths carried them far, but whose small weaknesses ultimately made the difference when it mattered most.</p>



